 <sec class="sec">
  <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">3.1.2. The Ultra-Cold Limit</div>
  <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">In the ultra-cold energy range (below 0.001 meV) only 
   <span class="italic">J</span> = 0 contributes to the partial wave expansion in Equation (6), so that the dependence of ics on collision energy follows the limiting behavior well-described by the Wigner's threshold law (Wigner, 
   <a rid="B63" ref-type="bibr" href="#B63">1948</a>):
  </p>
  <div id="E9" class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
   <span class="label">(8)</span>
