  <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">In reference Bodo et al. (
   <a rid="B14" ref-type="bibr" href="#B14">2004</a>), analyzing elastic and reactive 
   <span class="italic">J</span>=0 reaction probabilities obtained with the SW PES, the authors were able to obtain the real and imaginary parts of the scattering length. The values obtained were 
   <span class="italic">a</span> = (−2.0−6.3 × 10
