   <a rid="T2" ref-type="table" href="#T2">Table 2</a> we can see that the imaginary part of the scattering lengths is in perfect agreement with our results. The negative value obtained for the real part of the scattering length for H
   <sub>2</sub> is attributed to the presence of a virtual state associated with the van der Waals well in the entrance channel and located around 0.3 meV below the reactive threshold. Fingerprints of this effect can also be noted in the left panel of 
   <a ref-type="fig" rid="F1" href="#F1">Figure 1</a>, where the SW PES curve shows up a faster increase around to 0.01 meV before reaching the Wigner regime. Additional evidences will be given later. For the F+D
   <sub>2</sub> reaction, the positive value of the real part of the scattering length suggests that the scattering may be influenced by a resonance state. However, no structure has been detected in the reactive observables.
  </p>
